name: Azure
address: Jl. Pangeran Sambit No. 747, Berau Indonesia

reviews.text: I must confess after all the travel to get it tho destination, I wasn‚Äôt feeling adventurous and I ordered the beef burger (hamburger). I enjoyed it and he fries that came with it were crispy and tasty. The reason to come here is convenience since it‚Äôs in the lobby of the Bumi Segah hotel. A friend had the crab fried rice and said it was fantastic.
reviews.title: Good food

reviews.text:
The taste of the cuisine are maintained best since the restaurant first opened in early 2014, and to this day is still the best in the city of Tanjung Redeb.

Try the fried kwee tiau menu is very tempting or burgers were amazingly delicious. Best restaurant and recommend to visit during stay in Berau
reviews.title: Remain the best in town

reviews.text: By location Azure is part of Bumi Segah Hotel, they have different variety of menu from Indonesian, Chinese to Western. However I find this place to be the only place in Berau that can serve a proper steak.
reviews.title: Western Food

reviews.text:
If you are bored of Indonesian food and looking for some International food then this place is not it. The menu is primarily Indonesian / Chinese food with some fancy plating to make it look western. They do have a couple of salads. Luckily they also provide the menu from the lobby which has dishes like chicken chop, cordon bleu, beef steak etc.
Even though I was the only one in the restaurant, I think I had to wait 30 min for my food- at least it's cooked fresh.¬†
Having said that the food looked great when it came. I ordered the cordon bleu. Not world class but delicious nonetheless even if it was a bit Asian style. Nice and clean environment. Relaxing music after a tiring day. What's there not to like?
reviews.title: Chill place. Clean environment

name: Pondok Pasundan Derizca
address: Jl H. Isa III Tanjung Redeb, Berau Indonesia

reviews.text:
The surrounding area seems to be undergoing construction with an empty piece of land directly opposite the restaurant. This restaurant looks like a hut made with dark wood/bamboo. Once inside it's a bright area and because it is covered with dark bamboo the area is actually very cooling. There is a buffet with more than 30 dishes - what a wonderful spread. There are different types of vegetables, fish curry, chicken, otak, many different types of soup etc. We could really pick our fill. The food was good but a bit cold. The seating is square tables with benches and of course a TV. The lady boss very friendly. 
The people I came with said its a lunch time restaurant, not really for dinner.
reviews.title: Gem in a rural area

reviews.text: makanannya banyak pilihan dan lumayan enak dan cocok di lidah lejat dan segar apalagi sambelnya. menu sundanya cukup lengkap segala macam pepes ada bahkan sampe semur jengkol pun ada.  selain itu menu system prasmanan, bebes untuk mengambil sndiri sesuai selera kita.

reviews.text: Masakannya lunayan enak, tempatnya bersih, cocok untuk menjamu kolega. Menu sundanya cukup lengkap segala macam pepes ada bahkan sampe semur jengkol pun ada. Harga lumayan mahal jika dibandingkan dengan masakan subda di bandung, tapi klo utk sekedar mengobati kerinduan masakan sunda saya rasa tidak masalah :)
reviews.title: A little bit pricey

reviews.text: Makanannya banyak pilihan n cocok dilidah...lezat dan segar...apalagi sambelnya, mantaaappp. Selain itu menu sistem prasmanan, bebas utk mengambil sendiri sesuai selera kita üòä

name: Padang Kuring Restaurant
address: Jl SM Aminuddin Tanjung Redeb, Berau Indonesia

reviews.text: With so many Padang restaurant available on Berau, this one stand out to be one with the most variety of menus. I recommend to visit during lunch hour to ensure all the dishes are still available.
reviews.title: Padang Food

reviews.text:
Everything was good, from the taste, services and various menu. It is really original taste of Padang flavor with the complete menu, such as Ayam Pop, Rendang, Kalio Ati, Gulai Otak and many more.

Try the Sate Padang as well, the best taste of Sate Padang in Tanjung Redeb
reviews.title: The best taste in town

reviews.text:
This restaurant is housed in a small building but when we came in, it was quite a big area and seems popular with the locals. However, the place doesn't seem as clean as some of the places we had been. The food had also been pre-cooked and kept in a small room where the service staff were smoking in. 
This place serves Nasi Padang - Indonesian food. When we arrived, they just started bringing plates and plates of food. We must have had more than 25 dishes - probably more seafood and meat than vegetables. Naturally the food was a little cold. Some of the more interesting dishes would be the dish of beef brain. My favourite dish was the fish done otak style.
reviews.title: Comprehensive Nasi Padang

reviews.text: Rumah makan dengan cita rasa minang yang cukup lumayan untuk di area sekitar kita Berau. Lokasi dekat dengan pusat kota
reviews.title: Cita Rasa Minang nya terasa

reviews.text: Puas dengan layanan yang diberikan.. menu komplit dan cepat penyajiannya. tidak terlalu lama menunggu..
reviews.title: Menu Komplit

reviews.text: Ini termasuk restoran padang dengan menu terlengkap dari sekian masakan padang yang ada di berau. Tempatnya bersih, pelayanan bagus, tapi sayang area merokok dan tidak merokok digabung jadi sedikit tidak nyaman pdhl diruangan itu ada ac nya. Utk harga standart berau (porsi skali makan 40-50rb).
reviews.title: Menu lengkap dekat pusat kota

reviews.text: Belum bisa disejajarkan dengan beberapa restoran Padang yang ada di kota-kota besar lain di Indonesia, tapi kalau Anda ingin menikmati masakan Padang dengan nikmat dan nyaman di kota Berau, di sinilah pilihan yang tepat.

reviews.text: Padang Kuring merupakan tempet yang sering saya kunjunngi ketika di Berau. Menu yang disajikan lezat, yang jadi favorit saya daging cincang dan udang bakar yang besaar. Trus disini juga ada sate padang looo...., menu yang ga pernah saya temukan di warung padang lain yang ada di Berau. Harga yang di berikan sedikit lebih tinggi namun sebanding dengan rasa makanannya...

reviews.text: If you are looking the best taste of Aceh Coffee, this is the right place in Tanjung Redeb of Berau. Serving with traditional Aceh manner and culture. Try also the side dishes, Mie Goreng Aceh - it won't let you down and stop to taste!!!

reviews.text: The cafe is by the river along many other cafes. This is a bit of a hole in the wall but this is where the locals come for their breakfast. We ordered the acheh coffee which is quite strong. There is also a kue which is like the rice dumplings with gula and dessicated coconut. The rice dumplings was pretty good.
reviews.title: Aceh Coffee and Kue for breakfast

name: Podo Tresno
address: Jl R. Ayub Simpang, Berau Indonesia

reviews.text:
This restaurant is located in a shophouse and the kitchen right in front. 
So after a few days of eating Indonesian food which can be oily and sweet, we will looking for somewhere a little less heavy food. This place was recommended for its fish soup - the fish is cooked in clear soup with the traditional sweet and sour taste that is Indonesian. It comes with rice and we could also order a myriad of dishes such as vegetables and fried fish. Absolutely delicious.
reviews.title: Yummy Fish Soup

name: Kahyangan Seafood and Chinese Restaurant
address: Jl Akb Sanipah Tanjung Redeb, Berau Indonesia
rankingString: #1 of 11 places to eat in Berau

reviews.text: Old style chinese food restaurant. The portion is huge and the taste is good. The only problem is the waiting time. Price is good.. 20k IDR to 50k
reviews.title: One of the best food in berau especially fasting month

reviews.text: I've been eating here so many times. Without any doubt I could stated that this restaurant served the best chinese food in town. My favorite menu are "ayam penyet" which is fried chicken served with fresh sambal and "mie goreng seafood" which is seafood fried noodles. The price is a bit expensive but it's worth every penny.
reviews.title: Best Chinese Restaurant in Town!

reviews.text: The place is clean with large wood table and wall fan. The food was prepared fresh immediately after our order from scratch. The fruit juice (mango and pineapple) are natural and so refreshing. We order sweet and sour prawn, Ayam penyet, garlic kankong and each dish was excellent . The family owner was also having dinner and offered us some yam. So yummy. A nice little restaurant in town with homemade cooking.
reviews.title: Unpretentious but  excellent dinner at Berau

reviews.text: The food is a Chinese style, well cooked and had good variety. It's not the best, but is something that you could have and enjoy. The pictures are a little outdated but not much has changed. Service was good, very hospitable.
reviews.title: Chinese food adapted to the local ingredients

reviews.text: Casual Chinese restaurant with very good, fresh food. We had asparagus soup, chicken and mushrooms, black pepper beef and ayam penyet - their speciality, spicy fried chicken. Recommended.
reviews.title: Good Food!

reviews.text:
A Chinese restaurant with a taste that is very remarkable, the whole dish was served up fresh and hot and fast. no need to wait too long to be able to enjoy an experience in a very original taste of seafood and vegetables.

Try the sweet and sour menu, from fish, squid, crab and shrimp and also try the special menu of kale hot plate served with tauco and plenty mushroom.
reviews.title: No comment - just try it!!!

reviews.text:
Supposedly the best Chinese restaurant in Berau. At the entrance before you go into the restaurant, there is open air kitchen by the road. When you enter the Resturant, it is bright and tables line the room and benches. At night, the environment is nice, breezy and clean although I am not sure whether it would be too hot during lunch. 
The menu is in Indonesian with no prices on the side. We ordered a few vegetable dishes and a lot of seafood. A lot of the repertoire is fried but when you taste each dish, it has a different taste. The chicken is free-range which is why it doesn't seem to have any fat. The prawns was delicious because of the batter it was fried in. The fish was caught fresh from from the river that runs through the town. We saw the owner eating his dinner. Since he caught us eyeing his food, he gave us the fried fish he had originally kept for himself. All in all, it was a good meal.
reviews.title: Best Chinese Restaurant in town

reviews.text: tempat makan ini sangat sederhana dan sangat menyenangkan, menyediakan Chinese food semua di sukai anak-anak saya dan anak-anak menikmati ayam penyet serta sambelnya ayam begitu empuk dan bumbu meresap, iak saos asem manis dan sayur-szyur lzinnya, harga juga terjangkau, semua menu yang di hidangkan sangat enak. patut di coba yaaa.

reviews.text: Restaurante chino pero regentado por indonesios (uno de nosotros habla chino pero no lo comprend√≠an bien), donde no hablan lenguas europeas. Pese a ello tenemos que reconocer que se esforzaron en atendernos lo mejor posible. Es un local sencillo, de grandes mesas con sillas de madera maciza, con la cocina a la vista. Pedimos un poco de todo gui√°ndonos por dibujos y dejando al azar muchas cosas... y todo estaba buen√≠simo (pollo, gambas, arroz, pescado...). En teor√≠a no sirven cerveza, como en tantos sitios de Indonesia, pero fueron a buscar y nos trajeron tres que pudimos compartir. Como postre tomamos unos batidos naturales estupendos -los tienen en la carta de zumos- de frutas o caf√© .
reviews.title: Comer√°s bien y barato aunque no tengas un idioma com√∫n

reviews.text: Sari Ponti Restaurant is our choice if you are craving for Chinese food on the island. They have variety choice of menu available, but I recommend their Crab. Price is a bit higher here however the quality of food is good.

reviews.text: The restaurant was spacious (2 story). The menu had many entrees.  A bit long for the food to arrive.  But the taste was just really good, so worth a visit despite a bit pricey.

reviews.text: As one alternative choices of the best restaurants in Tanjung Redeb. The menu featured are, like grilled prawns, fried snapper sweet sour, fried calamari, asparagus and kale hotplate. The price offered is quite reasonable compared with the taste of a given, but the service from the waiters is very poor. It took more than 30 minutes to get an extra plate and an extra white rice.
reviews.title: One of the best  Chinese-food Restaurants

reviews.text:
This is a stand alone building with two floors of restaurants. Downstairs is more for the general public. Upstairs quieter and for more corporate dinners. The place looks like a proper chinese restaurant with fans everywhere, different sorts of lights everywhere, Chinese lanterns and a TV that is always on. As a result, companies tend to come here for dinner and therefore the corresponding higher price. 
There is a wide selection of choice. Maybe more gimicky - they have a hot plate section and all the dishes come on a hotplate with stilts. We ordered the kangkong hotplate with garlic which was nice but a bit oily. Mee goreng was also good but Indonesian style so it's fried with sweet sauce. The dishes were however largely oily and forgettable.
reviews.title: Big and airy restaurant. Chinese food

reviews.text: Mencari makanan seafood di kota Tanjung Redeb sebenarnya tidaklah sulit karena kota tepian sungai ini disuplai banyak produk seafood dari pesisir Berau.  Namun untuk menjamu kolega dan makan beramai-ramai dengan suasana yang nyaman, bersih dan enak untuk ngobrol maka Sari Ponti bisa menjadi satu pilihan.  Kepiting, udang dan ikan kakap direkomendasikan menjadi menu pilihan.  Sayang satu saat kepiting lada hitam andalan pesanan saya dimasak terlalu pedas sehingga walau tetap bisa dimakan namun tak terlalu nikmat.  Perlu rupanya quality control dilakukan oleh manajemen rumah makan ini agar kualitasnya tetap terjaga.
reviews.title: Rumah Makan Seafood di Tanjung Redeb, Berau

name: Mama Bakery & Cafe
address: Jl. Durian I No.17, Tanjung Redeb Indonesia

reviews.text: Close by the hotels cluster in Tanjung Redeb, this bakery offers good quality goods and excellent coffee at a very fair price. It also has a food menu, which we didn't sample (I was put off by nachos with tartar sauce!) - but it may be worth trying.... Open from 09:00 daily.
reviews.title: Excellent coffee house and bakery
